An open letter appeared in the network, the authors of which - representatives of various social shooting organizations - demand the rejection of the "nonsense tightening" of the law.
The percentage of hooliganism with registered weapons is minimal, said Vasily Lesnikov, a lawyer and criminalist in an interview with the Russian BBC news agency.
According to the statistics of the Ministry of the Interior, 142 crimes were committed using firearms registered by the authorities of the Ministry of the Interior during the six months of 2012, while a total of 1168,000 crimes were committed during the same period.
The authors of the open letter are convinced that the tightening of legislation in the field of civil weapons will not force the perpetrator to switch to the "black" market.
According to them, any weapon can be found in Moscow at a low price.
Currently, the Ministry of the Interior claims that the situation with the proliferation of illegal weapons is under control.
Suppliers: from factories to officers
The "black" arms market is supplied by several channels.
The main channels are five, says retired Colonel Victor Baranec, who worked for ten years in the workplaces of the Ministry of Education and the General Staff.
Screenshot of sites that accept weapons orders
The first of them - "military or military route", that is, a weapon that was stolen during the fighting in the Caucasus.
